Czech Stocks Rise Most This Year on Emerging-Market Valuations

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-08-15T15:56:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-15/czech-stocks-rise-third-day-led-by-nwr-komercni-banka-erste.html
Czech shares rose the most in more
than eight months as Morgan Stanley recommended investors buy
emerging-market stocks, citing low valuations.  The PX equity gauge jumped 2.8 percent, the most since Dec.
1, to 1,016.8 at its 4:28 p.m. close in Prague.  Komercni Banka
AS (KOMB) , the Czech unit of Societe Generale SA, and  Erste Group Bank
AG (EBS)  of  Austria  advanced more than 5 percent. New World Resources
Plc, a coal producer, increased 8 percent.  The benchmark Czech equity gauge traded at 9.4 times
earnings today, up from 9.1 on Aug. 10, the lowest since 2008.
Morgan Stanley increased its equity allocation in its multi-
asset emerging-market portfolio to 58 percent, eight percentage
points over benchmark, and the most since April 2009, according
to a report today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
